{"name": "lxmfy", "metadata": {"name": "lxmfy", "version": "0.2.1", "classifiers": ["Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["lxmf", "rns"], "summary": "LXMF bot framework for creating bots for the Reticulum Network", "upload_time": 1735373707}, "documentation": ["# LXMFy\n\nEasily create LXMF bots for the Reticulum Network with this framework. Very similar to Discord.py.\n\n## Features\n\n- Hot reloading (Cog system)\n- Moderation commands (unban, stats, etc.)\n- Spam protection (rate limiting, command cooldown, warnings, banning)\n- Command prefix (set to None to process all messages as commands)\n- Announcements (announce in seconds, set to 0 to disable)\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install lxmfy\n```\n\n```\npoetry add lxmfy\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n**CLI Tool**\n\n```bash\nlxmfy create <bot_name>\n```\n\n**Python**\n\n```python\nfrom lxmfy import LXMFBot, load_cogs_from_directory\n\nbot = LXMFBot(\n    name=\"LXMFy Test Bot\", # Name of the bot that appears on the network.\n    announce=600, # Announce every 600 seconds, set to 0 to disable.\n    admins=[\"your_lxmf_hash_here\"], # List of admin hashes.\n    hot_reloading=True, # Enable hot reloading.\n    command_prefix=\"/\", # Set to None to process all messages as commands.\n    cogs_dir=\"cogs\", # Specify cogs directory name.\n    rate_limit=5, # 5 messages per minute\n    cooldown=5, # 5 seconds cooldown\n    max_warnings=3, # 3 warnings before ban\n    warning_timeout=300, # Warnings reset after 5 minutes\n)\n\n# Dynamically load all cogs\nload_cogs_from_directory(bot)\n\n@bot.command(name=\"ping\", description=\"Test if bot is responsive\")\ndef ping(ctx):\n    ctx.reply(\"Pong!\")\n\n# Admin Only Command\n@bot.command(name=\"echo\", description=\"Echo a message\", admin_only=True)\ndef echo(ctx, message: str):\n    ctx.reply(message)\n\nbot.run()\n```\n\nCredit to https://github.com/randogoth/lxmf-bot, helped me learning to create LXMF bots.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "lxmfy.commands", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "lxmfy.commands.command", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "lxmfy.commands.Command", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "lxmfy.commands.Command.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "description", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "admin_only", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "lxmfy.commands.Command.__call__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "lxmfy.commands.Command.__get__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "objtype", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Support instance methods"]}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "lxmfy.commands.Cog", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "lxmfy.commands.Cog.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "bot", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "lxmfy.cogs_core", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "lxmfy.cogs_core.load_cogs_from_directory", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "bot", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "directory", "type": null, "default": "...